  "text": "Definition 10 (GCFTB). For a given time constant and vectors ≻ ≻ 0, consider positive switched system (1) and cost function [CITATION_1] ; if there exist a feedback control law ( ) and a positive scalar * such that the closed-loop system is FTB with respect to ( , , , , ( )) and the cost function satisfies ≤ * , then the closed-loop system is called GCFTB, where * is a guaranteed cost value and ( ) is a guaranteed cost finite-time controller.",
